
Contributing to NJ Blogs üöÄ
First off, thank you for considering contributing to NJ Blogs! It‚Äôs people like you who help make this platform a more inclusive, voice-driven space for everyone.

As a project born from the Google AI & ElevenLabs Challenge, we value innovation, empathy, and clean code.
How Can You Contribute?
1. Reporting Bugs üêõ
If you find a bug, please open an Issue and include:

A clear, descriptive title.

Steps to reproduce the bug.

Your device/browser version.

2. Suggesting AI Features ‚ú®
We are always looking to improve our Gemini and ElevenLabs integrations. If you have an idea for:

Better prompt engineering for Gemini.

New voice personas using ElevenLabs.

Accessibility improvements for voice-navigation. Please start a Discussion in the "Ideas" tab!
Pull Requests (PRs) üíª
Fork the repository.

Create a branch (git checkout -b feature/AmazingFeature).

Commit your changes (git commit -m 'Add some AmazingFeature').

Push to the branch (git push origin feature/AmazingFeature).

Open a Pull Request.
Code Style & Standards
Keep it Clean: Follow standard Android/Kotlin (or React) styling guides.

Document AI Logic: If you change a prompt or an API call, explain why in the comments.

Respect the Community: All contributors must follow our Code of Conduct.
Testing
Before submitting a PR, please ensure:

The app builds without errors.

Your API keys are never committed to the repository (use .env files).

‚ù§Ô∏è Recognition
Contributors who have their PRs merged will be featured in our "Hall of Fame" in the README!
